uations]]\n[[Category:Systems engineering]]\n[[Category:Optimal control]]\n", "name_user": "A. Pichler", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eSee also", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dynamic_programming"}
{"title_page": "Sib\u00e9al N\u00ed Chasaide", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2019}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name             = Sib\u00e9al N\u00ed Chasaide\n| image            =\n| image_size       = \n| landscape        = \n| alt              = Sib\u00e9al N\u00ed Chasaide\n| caption          = \n| background       = solo_singer\n| birth_name       = \n| alias            = \n| birth_date       = {{birth year and age|1998}}\n| birth_place      = Ireland\n| origin           = [[R\u00e1th Chairn]]\n| genre            = Irish Folk\n| occupation       = \n| instrument       = \n| years_active     = 2016\u2013present\n| label            = \n| associated_acts  = \n| website          = {{URL|https://www.sibealofficial.com/}}\n}}\n'''Sib\u00e9al N\u00ed Chasaide'''  ({{IPA-ga|\u0283\u026a\u02c8b\u02b2e\u02d0l\u032a\u02e0 n\u02b2i\u02d0 \u02c8xas\u02e0ad\u02b2\u0259|}}; born 1998), known [[mononym]]ously as '''Sib\u00e9al''', is an Irish singer from the [[R\u00e1th Chairn]] [[Gaeltacht]], County Meath.<ref>https://www.facebook.com/crossborderorchestra/posts/1144240848942797</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/RTERnaG/videos/984671341575112/|title=Raidi\u00f3 na Gaeltachta (Oifigi\u00fail)|via=Facebook}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|date=26 March 2016|title=Young Gaeltacht vocalist brings Pearse poem to life|url=https://www.rte.ie/entertainment/2016/0326/777027-young-gaeltacht-vocalist/|publisher=|via=www.rte.ie}}</ref><ref name=\"songbird\">{{cite web|url=http://www.independent.ie/entertainment/music/music-news/songbird-sibeal-once-silenced-by-shyness-34593883.html|title=Songbird Sibeal once silenced by shyness|last=Horan|first=Niamh|date=3 April 2016|work=[[Independent.ie]]|accessdate=10 October 2016}}</ref> She is best known for her collaboration with  [[Patrick Cassidy (composer)|Patrick Cassidy]]<ref name=\"songbird\" /> singing his arrangement of [[Patrick Pearse]]'s ''[[Mise \u00c9ire]]'' at the [[Centenary (concert)|official government commemorations]] of the [[Easter Rising|1916 Rising]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.independent.ie/irish-news/1916/news-and-events/a-stroke-of-genius-to-kick-off-1916-celebrations-34329936.html|title=A stroke of genius to kick off 1916 celebrations|work=Independent.ie|accessdate=10 October 2016}}</ref><ref>{{Cite AV media|url=http://www.rte.ie/player/ie/show/the-year-of-the-rising-30004495/10667553/|title=The Year of The Rising|date=29 December 2016|publisher=[[RT\u00c9 One]]|accessdate=31 December 2016|url-access=limited}}</ref>\n\n==Discography==\n===Albums===\n* ''Sib\u00e9al'' (2019) No. 6 [[Irish Albums Chart]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://irma.ie/index.cfm?page=irish-charts&chart=Albums|title=IRMA \u2013 Irish Charts|publisher=[[Irish Recorded Music Association]]|accessdate=17 August 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Live albums===\n* ''Sib\u00e9al \u2013 Live at Abbey Road Studios'' (2019)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://umusic.ie/feature/new-irish-music-from-sibeal/|title=New Irish Music from Sibeal Ni Cassaide|website=Umusic Ireland}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.allmusic.com/artist/sib%C3%A9al-n%C3%AD-chasaide-mn0003495672/discography|title=Sib\u00e9al N\u00ed Chasaide &#124; Album Discography|website=AllMusic}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/sibeal-ni-chasaide-a-new-trad-music-star-is-born-zrhw33n8q|title=Sib\u00e9al N\u00ed Chasaide \u2014 a new trad music star is born|first=Lauren|last=Murphy|date=28 July 2019|via=www.thetimes.co.uk}}</ref>\n\n===Songs===\n* \"The Parting Glass\" (2018)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.allmusic.com/album/the-parting-glass-mw0003241354/releases|title=The Parting Glass - Sib\u00e9al N\u00ed Chasaide &#124; Releases|website=AllMusic}}</ref>\n* \"Human\" (2019)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.allmusic.com/album/human-mw0003249949/releases|title=Human - Sib\u00e9al N\u00ed Chasaide &#124; Releases|website=AllMusic}}</ref>\n* Traditional: Carrickfergus (arr. Pacey) (2019)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.allmusic.com/album/traditional-carrickfergus-arr-pacey-mw0003237071/releases|title=Traditional: Carrickfergus (arr. Pacey) - Sib\u00e9al N\u00ed Chasaide, Voces8 &#124; Releases|website=AllMusic}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Official website|https://www.sibealofficial.com/}}\n* {{IMDb name}}\n* [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=L6bENmhvxpk Clip of Sibeal Ni Chasaide - \"Mise \u00c9ire\" | The Late Late Show | RT\u00c9 One]\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Ni Chasaide, Sibeal}}\n[[Category:Irish singers]]\n[[Category:1998 births]]\n[[Category:21st-century Irish singers]]\n[[Category:People from County Meath]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Irish-language singers]]\n\n\n{{Ireland-singer-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2019}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name             = Sib\u00e9al N\u00ed Chasaide\n| image            =\n| image_size       = \n| landscape        = \n| alt              = Sib\u00e9al N\u00ed Chasaide\n| caption          = \n| background       = solo_singer\n| birth_name       = \n| alias            = \n| birth_date       = {{birth year and age|1998}}\n| birth_place      = Ireland\n| origin           = [[R\u00e1th Chairn]]\n| genre            = Irish Folk\n| occupation       = \n| instrument       = \n| years_active     = 2016\u2013present\n| label            = \n| associated_acts  = \n| website          = {{URL|https://www.sibealofficial.com/}}\n}}\n'''Sib\u00e9al N\u00ed Chasaide'''  ({{IPA-ga|\u0283\u026a\u02c8b\u02b2e\u02d0l\u032a\u02e0 n\u02b2i\u02d0 \u02c8xas\u02e0ad\u02b2\u0259|}}; born 1998), known [[mononym]]ously as '''Sib\u00e9al''', is an Irish singer from the [[R\u00e1th Chairn]] [[Gaeltacht]], County Meath.<ref>https://www.facebook.com/crossborderorchestra/posts/1144240848942797</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/RTERnaG/videos/984671341575112/|title=Raidi\u00f3 na Gaeltachta (Oifigi\u00fail)|via=Facebook}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|date=26 March 2016|title=Young Gael